Introduction

Denise is a South Korean-American singer-songwriter signed under CDNZA Records. She is a former member of the girl group SECRET NUMBER.

Denise first gained attention as a contestant on the competition show K-pop Star 5. After the show, she joined YG Entertainment as a trainee in May 2016 but left the company in 2018 after two years.

She debuted as a member of SECRET NUMBER on May 19, 2020, with the single album "Who Dis?". On September 29, 2021, Vine Entertainment announced that Denise would not participate in the group’s upcoming comeback due to contract negotiations. This announcement was followed by the reveal of the group's comeback, Fire Saturday, on October 27, 2021, with the addition of two new members.

On February 5, 2022, Denise confirmed her departure from SECRET NUMBER and Vine Entertainment through an Instagram post. She made her solo debut on December 29, 2022, with the EP "Me Before You".
